<item>
            <title>[LU-17546] using vfs_setxattr() and vfs_removexattr() from within osd leads to a deadlock</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17546</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;using vfs_setxattr() and vfs_removexattr() from within osd leads to a deadlock as those kernel helpers grab inode&apos;s lock first which breaks Lustre rule &quot;tx first, then locks&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
the problem was introduced with &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13430&quot; title=&quot;Rework __vfs_getxattr/__vfs_setxattr/__vfs_removexattr support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13430&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13430&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
